    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <persName type="from">Marquis d’Abrantes</persName> to
                                <gloss type="to">General Webb</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Botafoga</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-21">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear General</hi>: Allow me to fulfil the painful
                        duty to manifest to you my deep personal sorrow on the deplorable event
                        which has deprived your country of her so highly distinguished President,
                        Mr. Lincoln.</p>
                <p>But it may be said that the horrible act which has brought to a close his
                        existence has heightened him still more in the thankful citizens of the
                        United States, and insures him a still more renowned name in history.</p>
                <p>In wishing to your great and fair country every prosperity, I remain, with
                        the most perfect esteem and consideration, my dear general, your friend,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ABRANTES.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Watson Webb</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">Minister of the United States</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
